"title": "5595: trumpet",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5595: trumpet",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A musical instrument with a loud, piercing sound, used as a signal, both in times of war and of peace. It was also used extensively in Israelite worship and was frequently associated with divine activity.</p>\n<h2>Trumpets used to summon the Israelites</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:1-Num10:7\">NUM 10:1–10:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:13\">ISA 27:13</a></p>\n<h2>Trumpets sounded to announce religious festivals</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:8-Lev25:12\">LEV 25:8–25:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:24\">LEV 23:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:10\">NUM 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:1\">NUM 29:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:3-Ps81:4\">PSA 81:3–81:4</a> <em>The NIV usually translates the Hebrew word “shophar” as “trumpet”, but in this instance it is translated “ram's horn”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:15\">JOL 2:15</a></p>\n<h2>Trumpets sounded to attract public attention</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:1\">2SA 20:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:3\">1SA 13:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:2\">MAT 6:2</a></p>\n<h2>Trumpets blown to announce the accession of a king</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:39\">1KI 1:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:10\">2SA 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:34\">1KI 1:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:41-1Kgs1:43\">1KI 1:41–1:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:13\">2KI 9:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:14\">2KI 11:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:13\">2CH 23:13</a></p>\n<h2>Trumpets used to warn of impending danger</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:1\">JOL 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:5\">JER 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:1\">JER 6:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:17\">JER 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:1-Ezek33:6\">EZK 33:1–33:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:1\">HOS 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:6\">AMO 3:6</a></p>\n<h2>Use of the trumpet in war</h2>\n<h3>As a call to arms</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:33-Judg6:35\">JDG 6:33–6:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:27-Judg3:28\">JDG 3:27–3:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:16-Neh4:20\">NEH 4:16–4:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa18:3\">ISA 18:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:27\">JER 51:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:14\">EZK 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:8\">1CO 14:8</a></p>\n<h3>As a battle cry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:12\">2CH 13:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:2-Josh6:20\">JOS 6:2–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:8\">JDG 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:16-Judg7:22\">JDG 7:16–7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:14-2Chr13:15\">2CH 13:14–13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:24-Job39:25\">JOB 39:24–39:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:19-Jer4:21\">JER 4:19–4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer42:14\">JER 42:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:8\">HOS 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:2\">AMO 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:15-Zeph1:16\">ZEP 1:15–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>To signal retreat</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:28\">2SA 2:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:22\">2SA 20:22</a></p>\n<h2>Use of the trumpet in worship</h2>\n<h3>Played by priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:26\">2CH 29:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:10\">EZR 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:31-Neh12:36\">NEH 12:31–12:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:40-Neh12:42\">NEH 12:40–12:42</a></p>\n<h3>Played in the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:6\">1CH 16:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:24\">1CH 15:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:42\">1CH 16:42</a></p>\n<h3>Played in the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:12-2Chr5:13\">2CH 5:12–5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:13\">2KI 12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:6\">2CH 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:27-2Chr29:28\">2CH 29:27–29:28</a></p>\n<h3>Played to praise God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps150:3\">PSA 150:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:8\">1CH 13:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:14-2Chr15:15\">2CH 15:14–15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:28\">2CH 20:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:26\">2CH 29:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:40-Neh12:41\">NEH 12:40–12:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:4-Ps98:6\">PSA 98:4–98:6</a></p>\n<h3>Accompanying the ark of the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:28\">1CH 15:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:14-2Sam6:15\">2SA 6:14–6:15</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:4\">JOS 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:8\">JOS 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:13\">JOS 6:13</a></p>\n<h2>The trumpet associated with divine activity</h2>\n<h3>In visible manifestations of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:16-Exod19:19\">EXO 19:16–19:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:18\">EXO 20:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:14\">ZEC 9:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:18-Heb12:21\">HEB 12:18–12:21</a></p>\n<h3>At the second coming of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:31\">MAT 24:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:51-1Cor15:52\">1CO 15:51–15:52</a></p>\n<h3>In metaphorical use</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:1\">REV 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:1\">ISA 58:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:10\">REV 1:10</a></p>\n<h2>The trumpet associated with angelic activity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:2\">REV 8:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:6-Rev8:8\">REV 8:6–8:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:10\">REV 8:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:12-Rev8:13\">REV 8:12–8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:1\">REV 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:13-Rev9:14\">REV 9:13–9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:7\">REV 10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:15\">REV 11:15</a></p>\n<h2>Trumpets sometimes made from silver</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:2\">NUM 10:2</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Trumpets sometimes made from animal horn</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:4\">JOS 6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:13\">EXO 19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:3\">PSA 81:3</a></p>\n<h2>The trumpet in non-Israelite use</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:22\">REV 18:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:27\">JER 51:27</a></p>",
